# Data Catalog: Gold Layer

## 1. Overview
The Gold Layer is the final data layer in this Data Warehouse. The data here has been refined through the Silver Layer and is organized using a **Star Schema** (Fact & Dimension) to enable data analysts to easily build reports and dashboards.

---

## 2. Dimension Table: gold.dim_customers
**Purpose:** Stores comprehensive customer profile information, enriched with demographic data from CRM and geographic data from ERP.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **customer_key** | INT | Automatically generated *Surrogate Key* uniquely identifying each customer record. |
| **customer_id** | INT | The original unique customer ID from the CRM source system. |
| **customer_number** | VARCHAR(50) | Unique customer alphanumeric identifier (e.g., 'NAS12345'). |
| **first_name** | VARCHAR(50) | Customer's first name. |
| **last_name** | VARCHAR(50) | Customer's last name. |
| **country** | VARCHAR(50) | Customer's country of residence (Normalized from ERP). |
| **marital_status** | VARCHAR(50) | Marital status (e.g., 'Married', 'Single', 'n/a'). |
| **gender** | VARCHAR(50) | Gender (Primary source: CRM; Fallback: ERP data). |
| **birthdate** | DATE | Customer's date of birth. |
| **create_date** | DATE | The date when the customer record was originally created in the system. |

---

## 3. Dimension Table: gold.dim_products
**Tujuan:** Stores complete product attributes, including categories and sub-categories merged from CRM and ERP data.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **product_key** | INT | Automatically generated *Surrogate Key* uniquely identifying each product record. |
| **product_id** | INT | The unique product ID from the CRM system. |
| **product_number** | VARCHAR(50) | Product identifier code (e.g., 'AR-5381'). |
| **product_name** | VARCHAR(50) | Descriptive name of the product. |
| **category_id** | VARCHAR(50) | Product category ID (Linking to the ERP system). |
| **category** | VARCHAR(50) | High-level product classification (e.g., 'Bikes', 'Accessories'). |
| **subcategory** | VARCHAR(50) | More specific product classification. |
| **maintenance** | VARCHAR(50) | Indicates whether the product requires routine maintenance. |
| **cost** | INT | The unit cost or base price of the product. |
| **product_line** | VARCHAR(50) | Specific product series or line (e.g., 'Road', 'Mountain', 'Touring'). |
| **start_date** | DATE | The date when the product became available or was released. |

---

## 4. Fact Table: gold.fact_sales
**Purpose:** Stores transactional sales data as the central hub for business metrics. This table connects to dimension tables via surrogate keys.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **order_number** | VARCHAR(50) | Unique sales order identifier (e.g., 'SO54496'). |
| **product_key** | INT | Foreign key linking to the `gold.dim_products` table. |
| **customer_key** | INT | Foreign key linking to the `gold.dim_customers` table. |
| **order_date** | DATE | The date the order was placed. |
| **shipping_date** | DATE | The date the order was shipped to the customer. |
| **due_date** | DATE | The payment deadline for the order. |
| **sales_amount** | INT | Total monetary value of the sales transaction. |
| **quantity** | INT | Number of units sold in the transaction. |
| **price** | INT | Unit price of the product at the time of transaction. |

---

## 5. Table Relationships (Data Model)
- **fact_sales.customer_key** → **dim_customers.customer_key** (Many-to-One)
- **fact_sales.product_key** → **dim_products.product_key** (Many-to-One)
